  "texts": [
    "Our recent study demonstrated the impressive ability of GPT-3.5 in answering questions related to bariatric surgery, showing high accuracy, comprehensiveness, and reproducibility of responses [4].",
    "GPT-3.5's successor, GPT-4, was released in March of 2023 with improvements in performance across multiple domains [5][6][7][8].",
    "The current study builds on our previous analysis by comparing the accuracy and comprehensiveness of GPT-4 compared to GPT-3.5, in answering questions related to bariatric surgery.",
    "MethodsA total of 151 questions related to bariatric surgery sourced from healthcare institutions, and Facebook support groups were included.",
    "The methodology for question curation is described in our previous study [4]."
